name: DNA oxidative demethylase
classes: Acting on paired donors, with incorporation or reduction of molecular oxygen;
With 2-oxoglutarate as one donor, and incorporation of one atom of oxygen into each donor
reaction: DNA-base-CH3 + 2-oxoglutarate + O2 = DNA-base + formaldehyde + succinate + CO2
comment: Contains iron; activity is slightly stimulated by ascorbate. Catalyses oxidative demethylation of the DNA base lesions N1-methyladenine, N3-methylcytosine, N1-methylguanine, and N3-methylthymine. It works better on single-stranded DNA (ssDNA) and is capable of repairing damaged bases in RNA.

references.title: AlkB-mediated oxidative demethylation reverses DNA damage in Escherichia coli.
A non-heme iron-mediated chemical demethylation in DNA and RNA.
Iron-catalysed oxidation intermediates captured in a DNA repair dioxygenase.
